kdown gsc-comment-content"><p dir=3D"auto">Hi,<br>
I am using a Raspberry Pi 4 Model B with 4GB RAM and have deployed a custom=
 YOLO detection model (best.pt) on it. The camera is accessed using the Pic=
amera2 library, and while it works, the camera feed lags significantly.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">I believe the lag is primarily due to the heavy best.pt mod=
el and the limited processing power of the Raspberry Pi. Despite adjusting =
the frame rate and resolution of the Picamera2 feed, the performance remain=
s slow and laggy.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">Here are the training parameters I used for the YOLO model:=
<br>
model.train(<br>
data=3D"data.yaml",          # Path to the data configuration file<br>
epochs=3D100,                # Number of training epochs<br>
imgsz=3D640,                 # Image size<br>
batch=3D16                   # Batch size<br>
)</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">Camera initialization and inference code snippet:</p>
<h1 dir=3D"auto">Load YOLO Custom model</h1>
<p dir=3D"auto">model =3D YOLO("models/best.pt")</p>
